    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-09T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="1278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.74/2–954: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1278<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-09T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 9, 1954—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 55. Limit distribution. For President,
                    copy for Acting Secretary. From Secretary. <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                        >Eden</persName> giving considerable concern here to Egyptian problem. Says
                    question of whether to try to settle with Egyptians will be dealt with Wednesday
                    Cabinet meeting. He is strongly urging that conditions are ripe now for
                    settlement, and he hopes Cabinet will go along, although he admits <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWS1">Winston</persName> very difficult.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
